        "title": "fix: migrate QQBot credential backups to SQLite KV",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- remove QQBot runtime imports from legacy JSON/JSONL cache files so session, known-user, and ref-index data are SQLite-only and disposable\n- add a QQBot setup/doctor legacy-state migration for credential backup JSON files into plugin SQLite KV\n- teach startup preflight to notice QQBot credential backups so read-only commands still trigger the migration path\n\n## Migration note\n\nQQBot session, known-user, and ref-index files are caches and are not migrated. Credential backups are persistent recovery data, so doctor/setup migrates them into the `qqbot` plugin KV namespace and then renames the legacy source.\n\nRefs #84313\nFollow-up to #84314\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/program/config-guard.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/state-migrations.test.ts extensions/qqbot/setup-entry.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/config/credential-backup.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/session/session-store.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/session/known-users.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/ref/store.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/platform-storage-laziness.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/data-paths.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test:changed`\n- `pnpm check:changed` on Testbox `tbx_01kt4badamnr325zffwfa5q54j`\n- `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n",
